<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15014a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15014a">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15014a"> 14(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Fr. Abraham Ryan</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&lsquo;Dr. Sigerson&rsquo; by Irish American]</font> &hellip; <mark>Father Abraham Ryan</mark>, the poet of the Confederacy, wore his hair as nature had given it, and I have a photograph of the late Archbishop Ryan of Philadelphia, taken when he was a young priest, in which his hair shows quite as long as Dr. Sigerson&apos;s. <small> <a name="TL18Apr25" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TL18Apr25"><cite title="source">The Leader</cite></a> (18 April 1925) 257/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15190a" href="c15all.htm#c15190a">VI.C.15:190(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
